commit.message:
fix(dired-open-xdg): Programs that want a shell when using xdg-open

Some programms such as mpv don't like it when xdg-open is called
without shell attached.

Use call-process-shell-command just does that.

Signed-off-by: Björn Bidar <bjorn.bidar@thaodan.de>

commit.message:
feat(dired-collapse): apply overlay optionally

Create a boolean customization variable dired-collapse-fontify to
control whether to apply the fontification overlay to collapsed dired
lines.

feat(dired-collapse): support-dired-omit-mode

When dired-omit-mode is active, decide whether to collapse a path
based upon the number of files that would be visible, ie. exclude the
omitted files from the count.
fix(collapse): Ensure dir actually readable before getting entries

fix(collapse): do not attempt collapsing on "nil" files

Sometimes dired-utils-get-filename returns nil, for example when the
file represents a dangling mount.  In these cases, we should simply
skip the line because there is nothing to collapse anyway.

Fixes #203

commit.message:
Fixes on defcustom types

* dired-avfs.el (dired-avfs-ignore-commands):
* dired-hacks-utils.el (dired-hacks-file-size-formatter): Change
types from symbol into function (unfortunately there is no command
type).

* dired-hacks-utils.el (dired-hacks-file-size-formatter):
* dired-open.el (dired-open-find-file-function): Change symbol
quotes into function quotes.

* dired-avfs.el (dired-avfs-file-size-threshold):
* dired-images.el (di-thumb-relief): (di-thumb-margin):
(di-thumb-width): (di-thumb-height):
* dired-ranger.el (dired-ranger-copy-ring-size):
* dired-subtree.el (dired-subtree-cycle-depth): Change types from
integer into natnum.

* dired-narrow.el (dired-narrow-blink-time): Change type from
float to number.

* dired-hacks-utils.el (dired-hacks-datetime-regexp):
* dired-subtree.el (dired-subtree-ignored-regexp): Change types
from string into regexp.

* dired-narrow.el (dired-narrow-blink-time):
(dired-narrow-enable-blinking):
* dired-open.el (dired-open-functions):
(dired-open-query-before-exit): (dired-open-use-nohup): Reword
docstrings.

In dired-list.el, `dired-list-use-N-flag' will be obsolete as of
Emacs 30.1.
